<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-14T07:58:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-14T07:58:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/698</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Odessa</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RJA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Odessa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-14T15:00:00+02:02"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            14, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 20, 9.30
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In view of the situation in Petrograd the revolutionary committees of
                                Odessa, representing conflicting national policies, have agreed to
                                cooperate to maintain order locally with the result that normal life
                                in the city continues undisturbed. Outlook uncertain.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_RJA1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Ray</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>